        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-11-08T11:45:23.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Verget use screw caps for everything now, except for a few markets that demand DIAMs. Jean-Marie\u2019s line is that winemakers don\u2019t like screw caps because if there\u2019s a problem with the wine, \u201ceveryone will know it was them that screwed it\u201d. He uses DIAMs for Guffens-Heynen however.</p>",
